<br>
I have started a part time char here on fiona like most of use and got him to  just into 10th level and the past 2 weeks( dont play much as time is limited).  I was not looking forward to leveling 10 to 20 as it some of the most irritating leveling  in my opinion.  So i go to thinking about the fact that we have no drop perty much removed from almost all items.  The i rememberd the quest in fiona vie for the red head bands of gobo raiders. <br>
<br>
The interesting thing about that quest is that the same red head band drop of  gobo  watchers in  lOIO and warsilk woods( uncommon drop).  So I  moved my druid to kunark and headed to warsilk woods and hunted some watchers got some head bands ( 16 ).  ran back to fiona and turned them in.  The EXP is phenomenal!   and you get upto 1pp plus a wooden shield (sells for 8gp) for every 4 red head bands you turn.<br>
<br>
So i headed back to warsilk  made a lizard on my second account to see if merchants had any head bands for sale!  they did  and with money i got from quest and other money i had i purchased a full load of 64 head bands.  I repeated this proccess till i had purchased all head band at merchants in LOIO and WArsilks woods.<br>
<br>
Anyways to make this story shorter   I started this quest on friday  by last night sat when i logged i was level 17.  took me a long time to embty all the merchant in warsilk and LOIO.  as a lot of the red head bands were buried.   The exp from this quest is just amazing!<br>
<br>
After all said and done  I started friday with 30pp in the bank  and level 10.  ended saturday at level 17 with 50pp in the bank.   The red head bands are purchased at 1sp each from lizard merchants.  The gobo watchers at trivial at level 11 so i recommend if you going to hunt them do so at level 8 ( the red head bands are magic item so if mobs trivial you wont get them from kills).  <br>
<br>
I hope this helps people out.<br>
<br>
ps.  you might wait till after patch to try to buy red head bands from lizard merchant since i cleaned them out  as of sat night.<br>
