<br>
Oh, but wait.  This server isn't about leveling.  The primary concern is roleplaying.<br>
<br>
I think ALL levels are fun.  Heck, my little level one self zooming around Greater Faydark was so cute.  I ran over to Butcherblock Mountains to rid the world of the foul-smelling skunk population.  I managed to chat with those around me, further my RP storyline, and gain a little experience all at the same time.  I've had a ball since I began on this server.<br>
<br>
Now I'm level ten... Usually, this is my least favorite level.  Untwinked, you have to group.  Grouped, there's not a lotta stuff to kill real fast.  I don't care now, and that's the beauty of it.  Why, my little level 10 song mistress roams Freeport, city of men, trying to become comfortable in her surroundings.  She's already explored the Karanas and Erudin and has loved every minute of it.  That's why this server is so awesome.<br>
<br>
I think I'm going to defend him here... On our other servers, where we romp about with our little level 50s, we've seen powerleveling in our days.  Whether we powerleveled others or received help from a high level cleric or druid, we've probably been helped one way or another.  If you haven't, excuse my blanket-statement.  It, uh, doesn't apply to you.  Almost everything is fixable... except defense.  And dr00ids don't need defense anyway because they just sit around and farm stuff.  But not anymore because there is a TRIVIAL LOOT CODE!  HAHAH!  Which reminds me, has anyone else noticed a lack of druids? *GRINS*<br>
<br>
He came on this forum trying to suggest ways to level fast if you didn't like 10 through 20, and he got yelled at.  I feel some pity for the little guy, he was only trying to share a secret.  You may not like what he did; I wouldn't do this.  But isn't this just like buying belts from orcs and turning them in?<br>
<br>
I guess I just pity the guy for trying to help out and getting burned for it.  I don't like powerleveling; my cleric doesn't do it and I don't accept it.  I like to take things slow.  This doesn't mean that I'm going to go out and burn everyone who feels differently.<br>
<br>
